    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em>You trace paths of elemental fury across the battlefield.</em></p><p><strong>Prerequisites</strong>: Two Elemental Flux maneuvers known, two Foolâ€™s Errand maneuvers known.</p><p><strong>Benefit</strong>: While you maintain an Elemental Flux stance, whenever you move as part of a maneuver or combat maneuver, or force creatures to move as part of a maneuver or combat maneuver (including when dragging a locked creature), you and those creatures leave behind a trail of energy in every square exited during the movement. Creatures entering or passing through a trail takes points of damage equal to your initiation modifier of your active element's associated energy type. A creature can only take this damage once per action; for example, if a creature moved (or was dragged) across a trail multiple times in the same action, they would only take the damage once. Each trail you create with this feat is considered to be part of the same trail for the purposes of damaging creatures multiple times, and your trails vanish one round after you make them. You do not take damage from your own trails, and may suppress or resume this ability as a free action. This is a supernatural ability.</p>",
